  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ae4ce6e0954909147ab3c2dbfee869a6, type: 3}
  m_Name: RuinWatcher
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueScriptableObj
  entries:
  - text:
    - So it begins...
    - 'An age has passed since anyone''s come up that way from beyond the ancient
      springs. '
    - Not since the old kingdom fell to ashes and ruin.
    - Ah, but I must be getting ahead of myself.
    - I'm the watcher of these ruins. The caretaker.
    - Keep going on and up, and you'll reach the old road soon enough. Though I can't
      imagine why you want to go that way.
    - But you must be cautious. The shadow spreads. The road is no longer safe, not
      anymore.
    - 'You''ll be needing a weapon if you hope to survive. '
    - Unfortunately, I don't have any to spare, but you may be able to lay claim
      to a forgotten weapon up on the road.
    - Good luck, wherever you're going. May your paths lead you far from the Shadow.
    condition: {fileID: 0}
    priority: 0
